Upgrade VMware Tools in a virtual machine using the GUI:

Power on the virtual machine.

In the Navigator panel on the left side of the screen, in the Virtual Machines
list, right click on the virtual machine name and select
Guest OS -> Upgrade VMware Tools

Wait for the operation "Upgrade Tools" for the desired VM target to show
"Completed sucessfully" in the Result field of the "Recent Tasks" panel at the
bottom of the screen.  The process may take a couple of minutes.

Reboot the virtual machine.

If desired, shut down and back up the virtual machine.
